, rather than any other party, was because it was concerned that PG Bison was likely to set up its own internal formaldehyde plant which would have a negative impact on Woodchem who sells 93% of its production to PG Bison. If that happened, FirstRand could
 lose its largest customer. The proposed transaction will therefore enable Woodchem to remain a viable business.}
