oducts. Approximately 87% of all formaldehyde produced in South Africa is used for the production of formaldehyde resin. A small quantity of raw formaldehyde is also sold to other resin manufacturers as well as PG Bison who use it to produce melamine forma
ldehyde resin. For this reason we do not deal with the market for the manufacture of pure formaldehyde any further.}
